Class ParameterChangeWarningEvent

java.lang.Object
  |

        +--org.scec.param.event.ParameterChangeWarningEvent
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public class ParameterChangeWarningEvent
extends java.util.EventObject

Title:

Description:

This event is thrown when you try to modify a parameter's value beyond it's recommended value. This event gives the calling class the ability to either head the warnings or ignore it and update the parameter anyways.
